\f0\b\fs38 \cf2 A. A&P mechanic
\f1\b0\fs32 \
\
An FAA-certificated mechanic may perform maintenance, preventive maintenance, and alterations within rating and experience limits, and may approve for return to service as allowed under Part 65 and Part 43. A mechanic may not perform an annual inspection unless that mechanic also holds IA. A mechanic also cannot approve major repairs/major alterations in the same way an IA or properly rated repair station can when those approvals require approved data and post-work RTS authority.  \
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl324\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

