\fs48 \cf2 16) Codex-ready implementation instruction block
\f1\b0\fs32 \
Use this as your build brief:\
\
Build a role-based FAA maintenance and inspection workflow engine for myaircraft.us.\
\
Primary objectives:\
1. Classify each user request into one of:\
   - maintenance\
   - preventive maintenance\
   - inspection\
   - alteration\
   - major repair\
   - major alteration\
   - operational compliance check\
\
2. Determine governing regulation and workflow:\
   - 14 CFR 43.9 for maintenance/preventive maintenance/alteration records\
   - 14 CFR 43.11 for inspection records\
   - 14 CFR 91.409 for annual/100-hour/progressive applicability\
   - 14 CFR Part 43 Appendix D for annual/100-hour checklist groups\
   - 14 CFR Part 43 Appendix A for preventive maintenance vs major repair/alteration triggers\
   - 14 CFR Part 43 Appendix B and FAA Form 337 workflow for major repair/major alteration\
   - 14 CFR 91.417 for owner/operator record retention and status registers\
   - 14 CFR 91.411 / 91.413 / 91.207 / 91.171 for compliance checks\
   - 14 CFR 65.95 for IA-only privileges\
   - 14 CFR 145.201 for repair station privilege limitation logic\
   - 14 CFR 135.411 and Part 121/135 program logic for operator-program workflows\
\
3. Enforce role-based permissions:\
   - A&P may perform/sign ordinary maintenance and 100-hour where authorized\
   - IA required for annual and progressive signoff and post-major-repair/major-alteration approval path\
   - repair station may only work/sign within ratings and OpSpecs\
   - supervised non-certificated users cannot independently sign required inspections\
   - pilot may only perform and sign eligible preventive maintenance tasks\
\
4. Generate right-side editable draft output:\
   - work summary\
   - governing rule\
   - required signoff role\
   - editable logbook entry\
   - discrepancy section\
   - parts/materials section\
   - approval/disapproval statement\
   - signer block\
\
5. Show workflow checklist below generated entry:\
   - save to correct logbook(s)\
   - update digital records\
   - update current status registers\
   - print/share/email PDF to owner/customer\
   - prompt physical logbook update\
   - prompt Form 337 if triggered\
   - prompt discrepancy list if unairworthy\
\
6. Maintain two data layers:\
   - event records\
   - current status registers\
\
7. Hard validations:\
   - prevent annual signoff by non-IA\
   - prevent repair station signoff outside rating\
   - prevent using 43.9 template for annual/100-hour if 43.11 required\
   - prevent closure of major alteration without 337 path\
   - require discrepancy list on inspection disapproval\
   - require affected logbook mapping before close\
\
8. Required logbook mapping engine:\
   - airframe\
   - engine\
   - propeller\
   - appliance/component\
   - major repair/alteration permanent file\
   - operator program record\
   - AD/status register\
\
9. Required buttons:\
   - Save Draft\
   - Save to Logbook\
   - Print\
   - Create PDF\
   - Share\
   - Email Owner/Customer\
   - Create Discrepancy List\
   - Start Form 337\
   - Mark Airworthy / Unairworthy\
\
10. Every closed event must update:\
   - inspection status\
   - due tracking\
   - AD status if impacted\
   - life-limited status if impacted\
   - total time references as needed\
   - permanent records if major alteration / installed 337 item\
\

